== 薪水 ==
截至2018年12月，八名选区和四名全区议员的年薪为140,161美元，而议会议长的年薪为21万美元。 <ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dchr.dc.gov/sites/default/files/dc/sites/dchr/publication/attachments/public_body_employee_information_09302018.pdf|title=DC Government Employee Listing|date=September 30, 2018|work=District of Columbia Department of Human Resources|accessdate=December 31, 2018|archive-date=2021-04-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210428031322/https://dchr.dc.gov/sites/default/files/dc/sites/dchr/publication/attachments/public_body_employee_information_09302018.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref> <ref>{{Cite web|title=D.C. mayor, council chair and attorney general would get $20,000 raises with new bill|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/local/dc-politics/dc-mayor-council-chair-and-attorney-general-would-get-20k-raises-with-new-bill/2018/10/12/3693de9e-ce50-11e8-a3e6-44daa3d35ede_story.html|accessdate=December 31, 2018|work=Washington Post|archive-date=2020-11-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201109015938/https://www.washingtonpost.com/local/dc-politics/dc-mayor-council-chair-and-attorney-general-would-get-20k-raises-with-new-bill/2018/10/12/3693de9e-ce50-11e8-a3e6-44daa3d35ede_story.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>根据[[华盛顿邮报|《华盛顿邮报》]] 2011年的一篇文章，华盛顿特区议会议员是美国大城市中薪水第二高的地方议员。 <ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2011/02/02/AR2011020202953.html|title=D.C. Council Salaries are second-highest among big U.S. cities|work=Washington Post|accessdate=June 29, 2017|date=February 2, 2011|author=Craig|first=Tim|archive-date=2019-01-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190101145359/http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2011/02/02/AR2011020202953.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>

